Note: ===================================================================
Note: SOLIDITY TO HIR TRANSLATOR
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Translates Solidity AST to High-level Intermediate Representation (HIR).
Note: Maps Solidity smart contract constructs (contracts, events, modifiers) to HIR.

Note: Part of the Translation Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/solidity/solidity_to_hir.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Note:
HIR PRODUCER MODEL (model 1, typed hir_nodes.runa surface)
==========================================================
Solidity lowers onto the canonical hir_nodes.runa producer surface, the same
family ruby/dart/java use. The real hir_nodes API uses short creators
(hir_create_binary_expr), zero-arg declaration creators paired with setters
(hir_create_class then hir_set_class_name), a single module declarations list
(hir_add_declaration) and a single class member list (hir_add_class_member) -
there is NO per-kind module collection (no hir_module_add_class) and NO separate
field/method lists on a class. Every Solidity-specific construct that HIR has no
native slot for is carried as a string-keyed metadata property via
hir_set_metadata, and the hir_to_solidity backend reconstructs the exact Solidity
spelling from those keys.

Declaration storage decisions:
  contract / interface / library -> HIR_CLASS, distinguished by "solidity_type"
      metadata; members (state vars, functions, events, modifiers, nested
      struct/enum) are appended with hir_add_class_member.
  struct  -> HIR_CLASS  ("solidity_type"="struct"), fields are HIR_FIELD members.
  error   -> HIR_CLASS  ("solidity_type"="error"), parameters are HIR_FIELD members.
  enum    -> HIR_ENUM, value names appended with hir_add_enum_value.
  state variable -> HIR_FIELD class member, type/visibility/mutability/initializer
      preserved as metadata.
  function / constructor / fallback / receive / event / modifier -> HIR_FUNCTION
      class members, distinguished by "solidity_type"; events carry "solidity_indexed"
      on indexed parameters, modifiers carry their `_;` placeholder body.
  pragma / using -> module-level metadata (compiler directives, not runtime nodes).
  import -> HIR_IMPORT attached with hir_add_import.

Number literals keep their EXACT Solidity lexeme (0x..., 1 ether, 1_000) as a HIR
string literal tagged "solidity_number"="true" so the backend re-emits them bare
(unquoted); string literals are plain HIR string literals; booleans are HIR bool
literals. Binary/unary operators map to the nearest HIR_OP_* code AND record the
exact Solidity operator string ("solidity_operator"/"solidity_unary_operator") so
operators with no HIR opcode (** << >> & | ^) round-trip losslessly.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/solidity/solidity_parser.runa" as SolidityParser

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TRANSLATION CONTEXT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translation cursor tracking the HIR module being built plus the
contract/function/scope contexts. Current pointers update as the
walker descends and restore as it ascends, so nested constructs
(modifier inside contract inside module) can resolve enclosing
context without backtracking.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Four Integer fields stored as a value-type struct. hir_module is the
top-level HIR module pointer; current_contract is the enclosing
class HIR (null at top-level); current_function is the enclosing
function HIR (null outside function bodies); current_scope is the
lexical scope cursor for variable resolution.
@End Implementation

Type called "TranslationContext":
    hir_module as Integer
    current_contract as Integer
    current_function as Integer
    current_scope as Integer
End Type

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MAIN TRANSLATION ENTRY POINT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public entry point: builds a translation context, walks the Solidity
AST, returns the assembled HIR module. The context's hir_module slot
holds the result accumulated through the walk.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
create_context returns a fresh context with an empty HIR module.
translate_program walks the AST top-down, registering each top-level
declaration into the module via hir_add_declaration/hir_add_import.
Returns ctx.hir_module.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_solidity_to_hir" takes solidity_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ctx be proc create_context
    proc translate_program with ctx, solidity_ast
    Return ctx.hir_module
End Process

@Reasoning:
Constructs a fresh translation context bound to a new HIR module
named "solidity_module". The named module lets downstream tooling
distinguish Solidity-derived HIR from other source languages.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Calls hir_create_module (no-arg) to allocate the underlying HIR
module, then hir_set_module_name to label it. Constructs a
TranslationContext value-type with hir_module set and the three
current_* cursors nulled out (we're at top-level on entry).
@End Implementation

Process called "create_context" returns Integer:
    Let hir_module be proc hir_create_module from HIR
    proc hir_set_module_name from HIR with hir_module, "solidity_module"

    Let ctx be a value of type TranslationContext with
        hir_module as hir_module,
        current_contract as 0,
        current_function as 0,
        current_scope as 0

    Return ctx
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: METADATA UTILITIES
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Generic accessor for Solidity AST metadata lists. The parser stores
metadata as a flat interleaved [key0, value0, key1, value1, ...]
ListCore, so a value lookup is a linear scan stepping two entries at a
time. Centralised here so translation routines don't repeat the
boilerplate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If metadata is null returns 0. Otherwise iterates in steps of 2,
comparing each even-index entry against the requested key via
string_equals; on match returns the following odd-index value entry.
Returns 0 when the key is absent.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_metadata_value" takes metadata as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If metadata is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with metadata
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let metadata_key be proc list_get from ListCore with metadata, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with metadata_key, key

        If matches is equal to 1:
            Let value_index be i plus 1
            If value_index is less than count:
                Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with metadata, value_index
                Return value
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 2
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Maps a Solidity binary-operator lexeme to the nearest HIR_OP_* opcode.
HIR carries a fixed opcode set; operators Solidity has that HIR does
not name directly (** exponent, & | ^ bitwise, << >> shifts) lower to
the closest structural opcode and are disambiguated by the
"solidity_operator" metadata the caller attaches, so the backend
re-emits the exact token. The cascade is an unrolled string_equals
ladder ordered roughly by frequency; an unknown operator falls back to
HIR_OP_ADD as a structural carrier (still recovered verbatim from
metadata).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
string_equals comparisons against each known Solidity operator,
returning the matching HIR.HIR_OP_* constant.
@End Implementation

Process called "map_solidity_binop_to_hir" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "+" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "-" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_SUBTRACT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "*" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "/" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "%" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MODULO
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "**" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "==" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "!=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_NOT_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_THAN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_THAN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "&&" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_AND
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "||" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_OR
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "&" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_AND
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "|" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_OR
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "^" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_XOR
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<<" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_SHIFT_LEFT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">>" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_SHIFT_RIGHT
    End If

    Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
End Process

@Reasoning:
Maps a Solidity prefix/postfix unary operator lexeme to the nearest
HIR_OP_* opcode. Solidity unary forms are ! (logical not), - (negate),
~ (bitwise not), ++ (increment), -- (decrement), and the `delete`
keyword. `delete` has no HIR opcode; it lowers to HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT
as a structural carrier and is disambiguated by the
"solidity_unary_operator" metadata, so the backend re-emits "delete".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
string_equals ladder over the five unary lexemes plus `delete`.
@End Implementation

Process called "map_solidity_unop_to_hir" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "!" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "-" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_NEGATE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "~" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_NOT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "++" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_INCREMENT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "--" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DECREMENT
    End If

    Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PROGRAM TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Walks the program AST iterating top-level declarations in source
order. Each child is dispatched through translate_top_level_declaration
to its kind-specific handler.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads children list via solidity_ast_children. Iterates list calling
translate_top_level_declaration on each. No early termination -
errors handled at child-handler level via metadata.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_program" takes ctx as Integer, program_node as Integer:
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with program_node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        proc translate_top_level_declaration with ctx, child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TOP-LEVEL DECLARATION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level declaration dispatcher. Solidity has seven top-level kinds:
pragma, import, contract, interface, library, using, error. Each
maps to a specialised translator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads node_type via solidity_ast_type. Nested If-chain comparing
against each SolidityParser.SOL_* constant; on match invokes the
corresponding translator and returns.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_top_level_declaration" takes ctx as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with node

    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PRAGMA:
        proc translate_pragma with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_IMPORT:
        proc translate_import with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_CONTRACT:
        proc translate_contract with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_INTERFACE:
        proc translate_interface with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_LIBRARY:
        proc translate_library with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_USING:
        proc translate_using with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_ERROR:
        proc translate_error_definition with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_STRUCT:
        proc translate_struct with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_ENUM:
        proc translate_enum with ctx, node
        Return
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PRAGMA TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity `pragma solidity ^0.8.0;` directives are recorded as module
metadata rather than as HIR declarations because they affect compiler
behaviour, not the runtime semantics of the contract.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads pragma_type (the directive name like "solidity") and metadata
list containing the value. Sets two metadata fields on the HIR
module: "solidity_pragma_type" and "solidity_pragma_value" (only if
value is non-empty).
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_pragma" takes ctx as Integer, pragma_node as Integer:
    Let pragma_type be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with pragma_node
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with pragma_node

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with ctx.hir_module, "solidity_pragma_type", pragma_type

    Let value be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "value"
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Let value_len be proc string_length from StringCore with value
        If value_len is greater than 0:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with ctx.hir_module, "solidity_pragma_value", value
        End If
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: IMPORT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translates `import "path";` and `import "path" as Name;` to a HIR
import node attached to the module. Alias (if present) becomes
metadata on the import.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads metadata, extracts "path" and "alias" via get_metadata_value.
Creates HIR import via hir_create_import, sets the path with
hir_set_import_path, attaches it to the module with hir_add_import. If
alias is non-empty, attaches as "solidity_alias" metadata on the
import.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_import" takes ctx as Integer, import_node as Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with import_node
    Let path be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "path"

    Let hir_import be proc hir_create_import from HIR
    proc hir_set_import_path from HIR with hir_import, path
    proc hir_add_import from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_import

    Let alias be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "alias"
    If alias is not equal to 0:
        Let alias_len be proc string_length from StringCore with alias
        If alias_len is greater than 0:
            proc hir_set_import_alias from HIR with hir_import, alias
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_import, "solidity_alias", alias
        End If
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CONTRACT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translates a Solidity `contract` declaration to a HIR class with
"solidity_type"="contract" metadata so downstream tooling knows it
came from Solidity (versus a generic class). Inheritance is captured
through metadata since HIR's class model doesn't natively know about
Solidity's multiple-inheritance specifics.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads contract_name (value slot). Creates HIR class via hir_create_class
and names it via hir_set_class_name. Pushes ctx.current_contract. Sets
source_language and solidity_type metadata. Reads metadata for the
"abstract" flag and "bases" inheritance list; attaches as metadata.
Iterates contract children invoking translate_contract_member on each.
Adds the class to the module via hir_add_declaration. Restores
ctx.current_contract to 0 (we're leaving contract scope).
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_contract" takes ctx as TranslationContext, contract_node as Integer:
    Let contract_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with contract_node

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, contract_name
    Set ctx.current_contract to hir_class

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "solidity_type", "contract"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with contract_node
    Let is_abstract be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "abstract"
    If is_abstract is not equal to 0:
        Let abstract_len be proc string_length from StringCore with is_abstract
        If abstract_len is greater than 0:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "solidity_abstract", "true"
        End If
    End If

    Let bases be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "bases"
    If bases is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_inheritance with ctx, hir_class, bases
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with contract_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            proc translate_contract_member with ctx, child
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
    Set ctx.current_contract to 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records inheritance via metadata since HIR's basic class model doesn't
directly express Solidity's C3-linearized multiple-inheritance. Each
base class is added as a separate "solidity_inherits" metadata entry;
multiple sets with the same key accumulate into the node's property
list, which the backend re-reads with get_all_metadata_values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Copies the bases into a fresh ListCore and stores that single list
handle under "solidity_inherits" in one hir_set_metadata call. Storing a
list (rather than one set per base) is required because the HIR property
dictionary overwrites repeated keys - a per-base loop would keep only
the last base. The backend reads the list back via get_all_metadata_values.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_inheritance" takes ctx as Integer, hir_class as Integer, bases as Integer:
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with bases
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let inherits be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let base_name be proc list_get from ListCore with bases, i
        proc list_append from ListCore with inherits, base_name
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "solidity_inherits", inherits
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: INTERFACE TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity interfaces are like abstract contracts with only function
signatures (no implementations). HIR represents them as classes with
solidity_type="interface" metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Same shape as translate_contract: reads name, creates HIR class,
pushes current_contract, sets metadata (source_language, solidity_type
= "interface"), iterates members, adds to module via
hir_add_declaration, restores current_contract.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_interface" takes ctx as TranslationContext, interface_node as Integer:
    Let interface_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with interface_node

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, interface_name
    Set ctx.current_contract to hir_class

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "solidity_type", "interface"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with interface_node
    Let bases be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "bases"
    If bases is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_inheritance with ctx, hir_class, bases
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with interface_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            proc translate_contract_member with ctx, child
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
    Set ctx.current_contract to 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: LIBRARY TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity libraries are stateless code collections that can be called
via `using` directives or qualified `LibName.function()` syntax. HIR
treats them as classes with solidity_type="library" metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Same pattern as contract/interface: reads name, creates HIR class
with solidity_type="library" metadata, pushes current_contract,
translates members, adds to module via hir_add_declaration, restores
cursor.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_library" takes ctx as TranslationContext, library_node as Integer:
    Let library_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with library_node

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, library_name
    Set ctx.current_contract to hir_class

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "solidity_type", "library"

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with library_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            proc translate_contract_member with ctx, child
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
    Set ctx.current_contract to 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: USING DIRECTIVE TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity's `using LibName for Type;` directive attaches library
methods to a type so they can be called via dot notation. Recorded
as module (or contract) metadata since there's no direct HIR analog.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads library_name (the value slot) and target_type from metadata.
Attaches as metadata "solidity_using_library" and
"solidity_using_target" on the enclosing contract when inside one,
otherwise on the module.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_using" takes ctx as TranslationContext, using_node as Integer:
    Let library_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with using_node
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with using_node
    Let target_type be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "target"

    Let host be ctx.current_contract
    If host is equal to 0:
        Set host to ctx.hir_module
    End If

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with host, "solidity_using_library", library_name
    If target_type is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with host, "solidity_using_target", target_type
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: ERROR DEFINITION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity 0.8.4+ custom errors `error MyError(uint256 code);` are
exception-like types used with `revert` for cheaper error reporting.
HIR records them as classes with solidity_type="error" whose fields
hold the error parameters.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads error name, creates a HIR class with solidity_type="error"
metadata. Iterates parameter children, building a HIR field per
parameter (name + "solidity_field_type" metadata) appended via
hir_add_class_member. Errors declared inside a contract attach as a
member of the enclosing contract; file-scope errors attach to the
module.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_error_definition" takes ctx as TranslationContext, error_node as Integer:
    Let error_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with error_node

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, error_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "solidity_type", "error"

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with error_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let param_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with child
            Let param_metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with child
            Let param_type be proc get_metadata_value with param_metadata, "type"

            Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR
            proc hir_set_field_name from HIR with hir_field, param_name
            If param_type is not equal to 0:
                proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "solidity_field_type", param_type
            End If
            proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with hir_class, hir_field
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    If ctx.current_contract is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_class
    Otherwise:
        proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CONTRACT MEMBER TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Contract member dispatcher. Within a contract, members can be:
struct, enum, event, modifier, function, constructor, fallback,
receive, state variable, error (Solidity 0.8.4+), using, or nested
type. Each routes to its specialised translator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads node_type and dispatches via If-chain against the
SolidityParser.SOL_* constants for each member kind, calling the
corresponding translate_* handler.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_contract_member" takes ctx as Integer, member_node as Integer:
    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with member_node

    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_USING:
        proc translate_using with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_STRUCT:
        proc translate_struct with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_ENUM:
        proc translate_enum with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_EVENT:
        proc translate_event with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_ERROR:
        proc translate_error_definition with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_MODIFIER:
        proc translate_modifier with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_CONSTRUCTOR:
        proc translate_constructor with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_FALLBACK:
        proc translate_fallback with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_RECEIVE:
        proc translate_receive with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_FUNCTION:
        proc translate_function with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_STATE_VARIABLE:
        proc translate_state_variable with ctx, member_node
        Return
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STRUCT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translates `struct Name { field; field; }` to a HIR class with
solidity_type="struct". Struct fields map to HIR class fields whose
Solidity type is preserved in "solidity_field_type" metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads struct name, creates HIR class, attaches solidity_type metadata.
Iterates field children, building a HIR field per entry (name +
solidity_field_type) appended via hir_add_class_member. Nested structs
inside a contract attach as a member of the enclosing contract;
file-scope structs attach to the module.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_struct" takes ctx as TranslationContext, struct_node as Integer:
    Let struct_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with struct_node

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, struct_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "solidity_type", "struct"

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with struct_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let field_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with child
            Let field_metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with child
            Let field_type be proc get_metadata_value with field_metadata, "type"

            Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR
            proc hir_set_field_name from HIR with hir_field, field_name
            If field_type is not equal to 0:
                proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "solidity_field_type", field_type
            End If
            proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with hir_class, hir_field
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    If ctx.current_contract is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_class
    Otherwise:
        proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: ENUM TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translates `enum Name { A, B, C }` to a HIR enum whose value-name list
holds each constant in declared order. Solidity enums are
sequentially-numbered constants represented as uint values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads enum name, creates HIR enum via hir_create_enum + hir_set_enum_name
with solidity_type="enum" metadata. Reads the "values" metadata list and
appends each value name via hir_add_enum_value. Nested enums inside a
contract attach as a member of the enclosing contract; file-scope enums
attach to the module via hir_add_declaration.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_enum" takes ctx as TranslationContext, enum_node as Integer:
    Let enum_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with enum_node

    Let hir_enum be proc hir_create_enum from HIR
    proc hir_set_enum_name from HIR with hir_enum, enum_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_enum, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_enum, "solidity_type", "enum"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with enum_node
    Let values be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "values"

    If values is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with values
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let value_name be proc list_get from ListCore with values, i
            proc hir_add_enum_value from HIR with hir_enum, value_name
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    If ctx.current_contract is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_enum
    Otherwise:
        proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_enum
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EVENT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity events `event Name(args)` emit log entries on the
blockchain. HIR represents them as functions (since emit is a
call-like operation) with solidity_type="event" metadata to
distinguish them.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads event name, creates HIR function via hir_create_function +
hir_set_function_name with solidity_type="event" metadata. Iterates
parameter children adding each via build_parameter, tagging indexed
parameters with "solidity_indexed". Handles the "anonymous" flag.
Appended to the enclosing contract via hir_add_class_member.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_event" takes ctx as TranslationContext, event_node as Integer:
    Let event_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with event_node

    Let hir_event be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_event, event_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_event, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_event, "solidity_type", "event"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with event_node
    Let is_anonymous be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "anonymous"
    If is_anonymous is not equal to 0:
        Let anon_len be proc string_length from StringCore with is_anonymous
        If anon_len is greater than 0:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_event, "solidity_anonymous", "true"
        End If
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with event_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with child
            If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                Let hir_param be proc build_parameter with child
                Let param_metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with child
                Let is_indexed be proc get_metadata_value with param_metadata, "indexed"
                If is_indexed is not equal to 0:
                    Let indexed_len be proc string_length from StringCore with is_indexed
                    If indexed_len is greater than 0:
                        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_param, "solidity_indexed", "true"
                    End If
                End If
                proc hir_add_parameter from HIR with hir_event, hir_param
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_event
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MODIFIER TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity modifiers `modifier onlyOwner() { ...; _; }` are aspect-style
preconditions that wrap function bodies. HIR represents them as
functions with solidity_type="modifier" so consumers can decide whether
to inline them or keep them as named blocks. The `_;` placeholder lives
inside the modifier body block as an expression statement on an
identifier named "_".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads modifier name, creates HIR function. Sets solidity_type="modifier"
metadata. Iterates children: parameters become HIR parameters, the body
block lowers via translate_statement and is set with hir_set_function_body.
Appended to the enclosing contract via hir_add_class_member.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_modifier" takes ctx as TranslationContext, modifier_node as Integer:
    Let modifier_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with modifier_node

    Let hir_modifier be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_modifier, modifier_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_modifier, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_modifier, "solidity_type", "modifier"

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with modifier_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with child

            If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                Let hir_param be proc build_parameter with child
                proc hir_add_parameter from HIR with hir_modifier, hir_param
            Otherwise:
                If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                    Set ctx.current_function to hir_modifier
                    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
                    proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_modifier, hir_body
                    Set ctx.current_function to 0
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_modifier
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FUNCTION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity function with full metadata: visibility (public/private/
external/internal), state mutability (pure/view/payable), modifiers
list, return type. Each piece is captured on the HIR function so the
backend reconstructs the exact declaration.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads function name, creates HIR function, sets name. Reads metadata
for visibility/mutability/modifiers via translate_function_modifiers
and the "returns" return-type list. Iterates parameter children
(build_parameter + hir_add_parameter) and the body block (lowered via
translate_statement, set with hir_set_function_body). Appended to the
enclosing contract via hir_add_class_member.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_function" takes ctx as TranslationContext, function_node as Integer:
    Let function_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with function_node

    Let hir_function be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_function, function_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "solidity_type", "function"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with function_node
    proc translate_function_modifiers with ctx, hir_function, metadata

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with function_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with child

            If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                Let hir_param be proc build_parameter with child
                proc hir_add_parameter from HIR with hir_function, hir_param
            Otherwise:
                If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                    Set ctx.current_function to hir_function
                    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
                    proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_function, hir_body
                    Set ctx.current_function to 0
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Let return_types be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "returns"
    If return_types is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_return_parameters with hir_function, return_types
    End If

    proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_function
End Process

@Reasoning:
Solidity named return parameters `returns (uint256 total, bool ok)`
carry per-slot types and optional names. They are preserved on the HIR
function under the "solidity_return" multi-valued metadata key (one
"type name" string per slot) so the backend reconstructs the precise
`returns (...)` clause, including named return slots.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the return-type list. Each entry is either a SOL_PARAMETER
AST node (read its value=name and "type" metadata) or a bare type
string. Builds a "type[ name]" string and attaches it as a
"solidity_return" metadata value on the function.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_return_parameters" takes hir_function as Integer, return_types as Integer:
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with return_types
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let return_list be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let entry be proc list_get from ListCore with return_types, i
        Let entry_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with entry

        Let slot_text be ""
        If entry_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PARAMETER:
            Let entry_metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with entry
            Let ret_type be proc get_metadata_value with entry_metadata, "type"
            If ret_type is not equal to 0:
                Set slot_text to ret_type
            End If
            Let ret_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with entry
            If ret_name is not equal to 0:
                Let name_len be proc string_length from StringCore with ret_name
                If name_len is greater than 0:
                    Set slot_text to proc string_concat from StringUtils with slot_text, " "
                    Set slot_text to proc string_concat from StringUtils with slot_text, ret_name
                End If
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set slot_text to entry
        End If

        proc list_append from ListCore with return_list, slot_text
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "solidity_return", return_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Attaches Solidity function modifiers, visibility, and mutability as
metadata on the HIR function. Each modifier name (including the
visibility keyword public/private/internal/external and the mutability
keyword view/pure/payable, plus user modifiers like `onlyOwner` and
`virtual`/`override`) is recorded under the multi-valued
"solidity_modifier" key in declared order so the backend reproduces
the exact modifier tail.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the modifiers list from metadata. Iterates calling hir_set_metadata
on each with key "solidity_modifier".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_function_modifiers" takes ctx as Integer, hir_function as Integer, metadata as Integer:
    Let modifiers be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "modifiers"

    If modifiers is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with modifiers
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let mod_list be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let modifier be proc list_get from ListCore with modifiers, i
        proc list_append from ListCore with mod_list, modifier
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "solidity_modifier", mod_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a single HIR parameter node from a SOL_PARAMETER AST node,
preserving its Solidity type and storage location (memory/calldata/
storage) as metadata so the backend reconstructs the exact parameter
spelling. Shared by function/event/modifier/constructor parameter
lists so the per-parameter metadata wiring lives in one place.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a HIR parameter via hir_create_parameter, sets its name from
the AST value slot, and attaches "solidity_storage"/"solidity_type"
metadata from the parameter's metadata list when present. Returns the
parameter node (the caller appends it with hir_add_parameter).
@End Implementation

Process called "build_parameter" takes param_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let param_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with param_node
    Let hir_param be proc hir_create_parameter from HIR
    proc hir_set_parameter_name from HIR with hir_param, param_name

    Let param_metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with param_node
    Let param_type be proc get_metadata_value with param_metadata, "type"
    If param_type is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_param, "solidity_type", param_type
    End If

    Let storage_loc be proc get_metadata_value with param_metadata, "storage"
    If storage_loc is not equal to 0:
        Let storage_len be proc string_length from StringCore with storage_loc
        If storage_len is greater than 0:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_param, "solidity_storage", storage_loc
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_param
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CONSTRUCTOR TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity constructors run once at contract deployment. Represented as
HIR functions named "constructor" with solidity_type="constructor"
metadata so the backend emits the unnamed `constructor` keyword form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a HIR function named "constructor". Reads metadata for
modifiers via translate_function_modifiers. Iterates parameters and
body identically to a regular function. Appended via hir_add_class_member.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_constructor" takes ctx as TranslationContext, constructor_node as Integer:
    Let hir_constructor be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_constructor, "constructor"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_constructor, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_constructor, "solidity_type", "constructor"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with constructor_node
    proc translate_function_modifiers with ctx, hir_constructor, metadata

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with constructor_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with child

            If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                Let hir_param be proc build_parameter with child
                proc hir_add_parameter from HIR with hir_constructor, hir_param
            Otherwise:
                If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                    Set ctx.current_function to hir_constructor
                    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
                    proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_constructor, hir_body
                    Set ctx.current_function to 0
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_constructor
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FALLBACK AND RECEIVE TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Solidity `fallback()` function is invoked when a call has no matching
function selector or when ether is sent without data. HIR represents
as a named function with solidity_type="fallback".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates HIR function named "fallback" with solidity_type="fallback"
metadata. Reads modifiers, iterates parameters and body, appends via
hir_add_class_member.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_fallback" takes ctx as TranslationContext, fallback_node as Integer:
    Let hir_fallback be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_fallback, "fallback"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_fallback, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_fallback, "solidity_type", "fallback"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with fallback_node
    proc translate_function_modifiers with ctx, hir_fallback, metadata

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with fallback_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with child

            If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                Let hir_param be proc build_parameter with child
                proc hir_add_parameter from HIR with hir_fallback, hir_param
            Otherwise:
                If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                    Set ctx.current_function to hir_fallback
                    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
                    proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_fallback, hir_body
                    Set ctx.current_function to 0
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_fallback
End Process

@Reasoning:
Solidity 0.6.0+ `receive()` function is a specialised fallback for
plain ether transfers (no data). HIR represents as a named function
with solidity_type="receive".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates HIR function named "receive" with solidity_type="receive"
metadata. Reads modifiers, iterates parameters (usually empty) and
body, appends via hir_add_class_member.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_receive" takes ctx as TranslationContext, receive_node as Integer:
    Let hir_receive be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_receive, "receive"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_receive, "source_language", "solidity"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_receive, "solidity_type", "receive"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with receive_node
    proc translate_function_modifiers with ctx, hir_receive, metadata

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with receive_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with child

            If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                Let hir_param be proc build_parameter with child
                proc hir_add_parameter from HIR with hir_receive, hir_param
            Otherwise:
                If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                    Set ctx.current_function to hir_receive
                    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
                    proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_receive, hir_body
                    Set ctx.current_function to 0
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_receive
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATE VARIABLE TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
State variables persist on the blockchain across calls. Solidity
captures visibility (public/private/internal) and mutability
(constant/immutable) modifiers on state vars. HIR represents them
as class fields with attached metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads variable name (value slot). Creates a HIR field via
hir_create_field + hir_set_field_name, appended to the current
contract via hir_add_class_member. Attaches type ("solidity_type"),
each modifier ("solidity_modifier"), and initializer
("solidity_initializer") from the AST metadata.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_state_variable" takes ctx as TranslationContext, var_node as Integer:
    Let var_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with var_node

    Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR
    proc hir_set_field_name from HIR with hir_field, var_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "source_language", "solidity"

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with var_node
    Let var_type be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "type"
    If var_type is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "solidity_type", var_type
    End If

    Let modifiers be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "modifiers"
    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with modifiers
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let mod_list be proc list_create from ListCore
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than count:
                Let modifier be proc list_get from ListCore with modifiers, i
                proc list_append from ListCore with mod_list, modifier
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "solidity_modifier", mod_list
        End If
    End If

    Let initializer be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "initializer"
    If initializer is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "solidity_initializer", initializer
    End If

    proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with ctx.current_contract, hir_field
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATEMENT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Statement-kind dispatcher. Solidity has block, if, while, for,
do-while, return, emit, revert, try, expression-statement, plus
break/continue. Routes each to its translator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads node_type via solidity_ast_type and uses an If-chain to
dispatch against SolidityParser.SOL_*_STMT constants. Each match
returns the corresponding translate_* result.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_statement" takes ctx as Integer, stmt_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with stmt_node

    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
        Return proc translate_block with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_UNCHECKED_BLOCK:
        Return proc translate_block with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_IF_STMT:
        Return proc translate_if_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_WHILE_STMT:
        Return proc translate_while_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_FOR_STMT:
        Return proc translate_for_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_DO_WHILE_STMT:
        Return proc translate_do_while_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_RETURN_STMT:
        Return proc translate_return_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BREAK_STMT:
        Return proc hir_create_break from HIR
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_CONTINUE_STMT:
        Return proc hir_create_continue from HIR
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_EMIT_STMT:
        Return proc translate_emit_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_REVERT_STMT:
        Return proc translate_revert_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_TRY_STMT:
        Return proc translate_try_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_ASSEMBLY_BLOCK:
        Return proc translate_assembly_block with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_EXPRESSION_STMT:
        Return proc translate_expression_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Block statement `{ s1; s2; }`. Wraps a sequence of statements in a
HIR block node. The unchecked block `unchecked { ... }` reuses this
translator and is tagged so the backend re-emits the `unchecked`
keyword.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates HIR block, iterates children statements translating each
via translate_statement, appending to the block via hir_add_statement.
Tags SOL_UNCHECKED_BLOCK nodes with "solidity_unchecked"="true".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR

    Let block_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with block_node
    If block_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_UNCHECKED_BLOCK:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_block, "solidity_unchecked", "true"
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with block_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let hir_stmt be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
            If hir_stmt is not equal to 0:
                proc hir_add_statement from HIR with hir_block, hir_stmt
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
`if (cond) { then } else { else }`. Creates a zero-arg HIR if node and
wires its condition, then-branch, and optional else-branch with the
hir_set_if_* setters.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads condition from metadata; then/else branches from children.
Recursively translates each. Sets condition/then/else on the HIR if.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_if_statement" takes ctx as Integer, if_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with if_node
    Let condition be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "condition"

    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition

    Let hir_if be proc hir_create_if from HIR
    proc hir_set_if_condition from HIR with hir_if, hir_condition

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with if_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let then_stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            Let hir_then be proc translate_statement with ctx, then_stmt
            proc hir_set_if_then from HIR with hir_if, hir_then
        End If
        If count is greater than 1:
            Let else_stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
            Let hir_else be proc translate_statement with ctx, else_stmt
            proc hir_set_if_else from HIR with hir_if, hir_else
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_if
End Process

@Reasoning:
`while (cond) body`. Creates a zero-arg HIR while node and wires its
condition and body with hir_set_while_condition / hir_set_while_body.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads condition from metadata and body from children; recursively
translates both and sets them on the HIR while.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_while_statement" takes ctx as Integer, while_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with while_node
    Let condition be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "condition"

    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition

    Let hir_while be proc hir_create_while from HIR
    proc hir_set_while_condition from HIR with hir_while, hir_condition

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with while_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body
            proc hir_set_while_body from HIR with hir_while, hir_body
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_while
End Process

@Reasoning:
C-style `for (init; cond; update) body`. HIR has a native for node
(hir_create_for) with separate init/condition/update/body slots, so
the Solidity for maps directly onto it without lowering to a while -
preserving the loop's structure for the backend to re-emit the exact
`for (...)` form. Each of the three header slots is optional.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a zero-arg HIR for node. The init is a statement (declaration
or expression statement) lowered via translate_statement; condition
and update are expressions. Body is the single statement child. Each
present part is set with the matching hir_set_for_* setter.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_for_statement" takes ctx as Integer, for_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with for_node
    Let hir_for be proc hir_create_for from HIR

    Let init be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "init"
    If init is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_init be proc translate_statement with ctx, init
        If hir_init is not equal to 0:
            proc hir_set_for_init from HIR with hir_for, hir_init
        End If
    End If

    Let condition be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "condition"
    If condition is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
        proc hir_set_for_condition from HIR with hir_for, hir_condition
    End If

    Let update be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "update"
    If update is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_update be proc translate_expression with ctx, update
        proc hir_set_for_update from HIR with hir_for, hir_update
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with for_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body
            proc hir_set_for_body from HIR with hir_for, hir_body
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_for
End Process

@Reasoning:
`do body while (cond);` - body executes once before condition is
tested. HIR has a native do-while node (hir_create_do_while) with
body and condition slots, so the body-first semantics survive
directly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a zero-arg HIR do-while node. Reads body from children and
condition from metadata; recursively translates both and sets them
with hir_set_do_while_body / hir_set_do_while_condition.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_do_while_statement" takes ctx as Integer, do_while_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with do_while_node
    Let condition be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "condition"

    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition

    Let hir_do_while be proc hir_create_do_while from HIR
    proc hir_set_do_while_condition from HIR with hir_do_while, hir_condition

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with do_while_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body
            proc hir_set_do_while_body from HIR with hir_do_while, hir_body
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_do_while
End Process

@Reasoning:
`return value;` or bare `return;`. HIR return statement carries the
optional value expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads optional return expression from "value" metadata; if present,
translates via translate_expression and attaches with
hir_set_return_value. Otherwise emits a value-less return.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_return_statement" takes ctx as Integer, return_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with return_node
    Let value be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "value"

    Let hir_return be proc hir_create_return from HIR
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value
        proc hir_set_return_value from HIR with hir_return, hir_value
    End If

    Return hir_return
End Process

@Reasoning:
Solidity `emit EventName(args);` fires an event log. HIR translates
the inner call to a HIR call expression wrapped in an expression
statement tagged "solidity_emit"="true" so the backend re-emits the
`emit` keyword.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the event call expression child, recursively translates it,
wraps in an expression statement, and tags it solidity_emit.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_emit_statement" takes ctx as Integer, emit_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with emit_node
    Let hir_call be 0
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let call_expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            Set hir_call to proc translate_expression with ctx, call_expr
        End If
    End If

    Let hir_stmt be proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with hir_call
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_stmt, "solidity_emit", "true"
    Return hir_stmt
End Process

@Reasoning:
`revert();`, `revert("msg");` or `revert MyError(args);` aborts
execution. HIR models it as a throw statement tagged "solidity_revert"
so the backend re-emits `revert`; the thrown expression is the error
call / message, or a bare identifier when revert has no argument.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the optional argument child. If present, translates it as the
thrown expression. Otherwise creates a bare `revert` identifier as the
throw payload. Tags the throw "solidity_revert"="true".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_revert_statement" takes ctx as Integer, revert_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with revert_node
    Let count be 0
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Set count to proc list_length from ListCore with children
    End If

    Let hir_exception be 0
    If count is greater than 0:
        Let call_expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Set hir_exception to proc translate_expression with ctx, call_expr
    Otherwise:
        Set hir_exception to proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with "revert"
    End If

    Let hir_throw be proc hir_create_throw from HIR
    proc hir_set_throw_expression from HIR with hir_throw, hir_exception
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_throw, "solidity_revert", "true"
    Return hir_throw
End Process

@Reasoning:
`try expression returns (...) { success } catch ... { handler }` is
Solidity 0.6+ external-call error recovery. HIR represents it as a
try node whose try block holds the success body and whose catch
clauses hold the handlers; the try expression is preserved on the try
node as "solidity_try_expr" metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the try-call expression from "expression" metadata and translates
it. Iterates children: the first SOL_BLOCK_STMT is the success body
(set with hir_set_try_block), each SOL_CATCH_CLAUSE lowers via
translate_catch_clause and is added with hir_add_catch_clause.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_try_statement" takes ctx as Integer, try_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with try_node
    Let expression be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "expression"

    Let hir_try be proc hir_create_try from HIR

    If expression is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_try_expr be proc translate_expression with ctx, expression
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_try, "solidity_try_expr", hir_try_expr
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with try_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        Let body_set be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with child

            If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                If body_set is equal to 0:
                    Let hir_try_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
                    proc hir_set_try_block from HIR with hir_try, hir_try_body
                    Set body_set to 1
                End If
            Otherwise:
                If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_CATCH_CLAUSE:
                    Let hir_catch be proc translate_catch_clause with ctx, child
                    proc hir_add_catch_clause from HIR with hir_try, hir_catch
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return hir_try
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each catch clause has an optional catch-identifier (Error / Panic /
low-level) plus optional parameter binding and a body block. HIR's
catch node carries a catch variable and a body block.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Scans children: the first SOL_PARAMETER supplies the catch variable
name (defaulting to "error"), the SOL_BLOCK_STMT supplies the body.
Builds a HIR catch via hir_create_catch and wires the variable and
body with hir_set_catch_variable / hir_set_catch_body.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_catch_clause" takes ctx as Integer, catch_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_catch be proc hir_create_catch from HIR
    Let exception_var be "error"

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with catch_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with child

            If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                Set exception_var to proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with child
            Otherwise:
                If child_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                    Let hir_catch_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
                    proc hir_set_catch_body from HIR with hir_catch, hir_catch_body
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc hir_set_catch_variable from HIR with hir_catch, exception_var
    Return hir_catch
End Process

@Reasoning:
Solidity inline `assembly { ... }` blocks contain Yul code that has no
HIR structural representation. The block is preserved verbatim as an
expression statement carrying the raw assembly body text in
"solidity_assembly" metadata so the backend re-emits it unchanged.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the raw body text from the node value slot, creates a HIR nop
expression-statement carrier, and stores the body under
"solidity_assembly".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_assembly_block" takes ctx as Integer, assembly_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let body_text be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with assembly_node
    Let hir_nop be proc hir_create_nop from HIR
    Let hir_stmt be proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with hir_nop
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_stmt, "solidity_assembly", body_text
    Return hir_stmt
End Process

@Reasoning:
Wraps a single expression as a statement (for side-effect calls and
assignments at statement level).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the wrapped expression child and recursively translates via
translate_expression, wrapping in a HIR expression-statement node.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_expression_statement" takes ctx as Integer, expr_stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with expr_stmt
    Let hir_expr be 0
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let expr_node be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            Set hir_expr to proc translate_expression with ctx, expr_node
        End If
    End If

    Let hir_stmt be proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with hir_expr
    Return hir_stmt
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EXPRESSION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Expression-kind dispatcher. Solidity expression kinds: binary, unary,
ternary, assign, call, new, member access, index, array literal,
identifier, literal. Each routes to its translator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads node_type via solidity_ast_type and dispatches via an If-chain
against SolidityParser.SOL_*_EXPR / SOL_*_LITERAL / SOL_IDENTIFIER
constants. Each match returns the corresponding translation result.
Number literals keep their exact lexeme as a string literal tagged
"solidity_number"; booleans become HIR bool literals; identifiers
become HIR identifiers.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_expression" takes ctx as Integer, expr_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If expr_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from SolidityParser with expr_node

    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BINARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_binary_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_UNARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_unary_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_TERNARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_ternary_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_ASSIGN_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_assign_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_CALL_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_call_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_NEW_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_new_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_MEMBER_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_member_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_INDEX_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_index_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_ARRAY_LITERAL:
        Return proc translate_array_literal with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_PAYABLE_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_payable_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_TYPE_CAST:
        Return proc translate_type_cast with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_NUMBER_LITERAL:
        Let num_value be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with expr_node
        Let hir_num be proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with num_value
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_num, "solidity_number", "true"
        Return hir_num
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_HEX_LITERAL:
        Let hex_value be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with expr_node
        Let hir_hex be proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with hex_value
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_hex, "solidity_number", "true"
        Return hir_hex
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_ADDRESS_LITERAL:
        Let addr_value be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with expr_node
        Let hir_addr be proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with addr_value
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_addr, "solidity_number", "true"
        Return hir_addr
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_STRING_LITERAL:
        Let str_value be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with expr_node
        Return proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with str_value
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_BOOLEAN_LITERAL:
        Let bool_value be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with expr_node
        Let is_true be proc string_equals from StringCore with bool_value, "true"
        Return proc hir_create_bool_literal from HIR with is_true
    End If
    If node_type is equal to SolidityParser.SOL_IDENTIFIER:
        Let name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with expr_node
        Return proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with name
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits HIR binary expression. Solidity binary operators include
arithmetic (+ - * / % **), comparison (== != < > <= >=), logical
(&& ||), bitwise (& | ^ << >>). The operator string lives in the node
value slot; left/right operands in metadata. The exact Solidity
operator spelling is preserved as "solidity_operator" so operators
that share an HIR opcode (or have none) round-trip losslessly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads operator (value slot) and left/right (metadata). Recursively
translates each operand, maps the operator to a HIR opcode, builds the
HIR binary node, and tags it with the source operator.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_binary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, binary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with binary_node
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with binary_node

    Let left be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "left"
    Let right be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "right"

    Let hir_left be proc translate_expression with ctx, left
    Let hir_right be proc translate_expression with ctx, right

    Let hir_op be proc map_solidity_binop_to_hir with operator
    Let hir_binary be proc hir_create_binary_expr from HIR with hir_op, hir_left, hir_right
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_binary, "solidity_operator", operator
    Return hir_binary
End Process

@Reasoning:
Unary expression: prefix (++, --, !, ~, -, delete) and postfix
(++, --). The "prefix" metadata flag distinguishes the two positions
so the backend re-emits `++x` versus `x++`. The exact operator is
preserved under "solidity_unary_operator".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads operator (value slot), operand and prefix flag from metadata.
Recursively translates operand, maps the operator, builds the HIR
unary node, and tags it with the operator and prefix/postfix flag.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_unary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, unary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with unary_node
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with unary_node

    Let operand be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "operand"
    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with ctx, operand

    Let hir_op be proc map_solidity_unop_to_hir with operator
    Let hir_unary be proc hir_create_unary_expr from HIR with hir_op, hir_operand
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_unary, "solidity_unary_operator", operator

    Let prefix be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "prefix"
    If prefix is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_unary, "solidity_prefix", "true"
    Otherwise:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_unary, "solidity_prefix", "false"
    End If

    Return hir_unary
End Process

@Reasoning:
Conditional expression `cond ? then : else`. Three operands stored in
metadata under "condition"/"then"/"else".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the three metadata operands, recursively translates each, and
constructs a HIR ternary node.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_ternary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, ternary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with ternary_node

    Let condition be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "condition"
    Let then_expr be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "then"
    Let else_expr be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "else"

    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
    Let hir_then be proc translate_expression with ctx, then_expr
    Let hir_else be proc translate_expression with ctx, else_expr

    Return proc hir_create_ternary_expr from HIR with hir_condition, hir_then, hir_else
End Process

@Reasoning:
Assignment `lhs = rhs` or compound `lhs += rhs`. Solidity assignments
are expressions; the operator string is preserved on the HIR assign
node so compound forms round-trip. Although the current parser folds
assignment through the binary-expression layer, this handler keeps the
SOL_ASSIGN_EXPR contract honoured for any assign node reaching the
translator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads operator (value slot) and target/value (metadata). Recursively
translates both operands and constructs a HIR assign node with the
operator preserved as both the HIR assign op-string and
"solidity_operator" metadata.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_assign_expression" takes ctx as Integer, assign_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with assign_node
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with assign_node

    Let target be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "target"
    Let value be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "value"

    Let hir_target be proc translate_expression with ctx, target
    Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value

    Let hir_assign be proc hir_create_assign_expr from HIR with hir_target, operator, hir_value
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_assign, "solidity_operator", operator
    Return hir_assign
End Process

@Reasoning:
Function call `f(args)`. The callee can be any expression yielding a
callable (identifier, member access, address.call). Stored as the
"function" metadata expression with arguments as children.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads callee from "function" metadata (recursively translated) or, if
absent, the node value as an identifier. Builds a HIR call expression
and appends each argument child via hir_add_argument.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_call_expression" takes ctx as Integer, call_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with call_node
    Let function be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "function"

    Let callee be 0
    If function is equal to 0:
        Let call_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with call_node
        Set callee to proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with call_name
    Otherwise:
        Set callee to proc translate_expression with ctx, function
    End If

    Let hir_call be proc hir_create_call_expr from HIR with callee

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with call_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let arg be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let hir_arg be proc translate_expression with ctx, arg
            If hir_arg is not equal to 0:
                proc hir_add_argument from HIR with hir_call, hir_arg
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return hir_call
End Process

@Reasoning:
`new Contract(args)` or `new Type[](size)` for array creation. HIR has
a native new node (hir_create_new) carrying the type name; the
constructor arguments are appended via hir_add_argument.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the target type from the node value slot, creates a HIR new node,
and appends each argument child translated via translate_expression.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_new_expression" takes ctx as Integer, new_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let type_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with new_node

    Let hir_new be proc hir_create_new from HIR with type_name

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with new_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let arg be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let hir_arg be proc translate_expression with ctx, arg
            If hir_arg is not equal to 0:
                proc hir_add_argument from HIR with hir_new, hir_arg
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return hir_new
End Process

@Reasoning:
Member access `x.y` for field/method/contract-member references. The
object lives in "object" metadata; the member name in the value slot.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads object metadata (recursively translated) and member name, then
constructs a HIR member-access node.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_member_expression" takes ctx as Integer, member_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let member_name be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with member_node
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with member_node

    Let object be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "object"
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object

    Return proc hir_create_member_expr from HIR with hir_object, member_name
End Process

@Reasoning:
Index access `a[i]` for arrays and mappings. Object and index live in
"object" / "index" metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads object and index metadata, recursively translates both, and
constructs a HIR index-access node.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_index_expression" takes ctx as Integer, index_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with index_node

    Let object be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "object"
    Let index be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "index"

    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object
    Let hir_index be proc translate_expression with ctx, index

    Return proc hir_create_index_expr from HIR with hir_object, hir_index
End Process

@Reasoning:
Array literal `[1, 2, 3]` creates an inline array. HIR's list literal
node holds the element expressions in order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a HIR list literal and appends each child element translated
via translate_expression with hir_add_list_element.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_array_literal" takes ctx as Integer, array_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_array be proc hir_create_list_literal from HIR

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with array_node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let element be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let hir_element be proc translate_expression with ctx, element
            If hir_element is not equal to 0:
                proc hir_add_list_element from HIR with hir_array, hir_element
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return hir_array
End Process

@Reasoning:
`payable(addr)` casts an address to the payable address type. HIR
models the cast as a call on a "payable" identifier tagged
"solidity_payable" so the backend re-emits the `payable(...)` form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the operand from "object" metadata (or the first child),
translates it, and wraps it in a call on a "payable" identifier with
the solidity_payable tag.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_payable_expression" takes ctx as Integer, payable_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with payable_node
    Let operand be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "object"

    If operand is equal to 0:
        Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with payable_node
        If children is not equal to 0:
            Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
            If count is greater than 0:
                Set operand to proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let callee be proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with "payable"
    Let hir_call be proc hir_create_call_expr from HIR with callee
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_call, "solidity_payable", "true"

    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with ctx, operand
    If hir_operand is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_add_argument from HIR with hir_call, hir_operand
    End If

    Return hir_call
End Process

@Reasoning:
A Solidity type cast `uint256(x)` converts a value to another type.
HIR's cast node carries the target-type name and the cast expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the target type from the value slot and the operand from "object"
metadata (or the first child); builds a HIR cast carrying the
expression and re-emits the type via the "solidity_cast_type" tag.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_type_cast" takes ctx as Integer, cast_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cast_type be proc solidity_ast_value from SolidityParser with cast_node
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from SolidityParser with cast_node
    Let operand be proc get_metadata_value with metadata, "object"

    If operand is equal to 0:
        Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from SolidityParser with cast_node
        If children is not equal to 0:
            Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
            If count is greater than 0:
                Set operand to proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let callee be proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with cast_type
    Let hir_call be proc hir_create_call_expr from HIR with callee
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_call, "solidity_cast", "true"

    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with ctx, operand
    If hir_operand is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_add_argument from HIR with hir_call, hir_operand
    End If

    Return hir_call
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PUBLIC API
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Alternative public entry point matching the file-level naming
convention. Functionally identical to translate_solidity_to_hir;
exists for API consistency with other frontends.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single-line wrapper delegating to translate_solidity_to_hir.
@End Implementation

Process called "solidity_to_hir" takes solidity_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc translate_solidity_to_hir with solidity_ast
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public single-arg facade invoked by the translation dispatcher's
LANG_SOLIDITY arm. Wires the full source -> HIR pipeline:
SolidityParser parse_solidity_source lexes + parses to a SOL_PROGRAM
AST root, then translate_solidity_to_hir walks the AST into HIR.
On parse failure (0 return from parse_solidity_source) the wrapper
short-circuits to 0.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
ast = SolidityParser.parse_solidity_source(source); if ast == 0
return 0; return translate_solidity_to_hir(ast).
@End Implementation

Process called "solidity_to_hir_from_source" takes source_code as Integer returns Integer:
    Let solidity_ast be proc parse_solidity_source from SolidityParser with source_code
    If solidity_ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc translate_solidity_to_hir with solidity_ast
End Process
